Barely a week after restoring diplomatic ties, Kenya has banned all flights to and from Somalia with immediate effect.   Although no reason was given, Kenya Civil Aviation Authority Director General Captain Gilbert Kibe said it was an order they are implementing and Kibe said he would not disclose details of who gave the orders and why.  This comes days after Qatar brokered a deal that saw Mogadishu and Nairobi restore their diplomatic relations.  Last week Somalia announced it had restored diplomatic ties with Kenya amid maritime boundary rows and pledged respect for sovereignty.  President Mohamed Farmaajo's spokesperson Abdirashid Hashi said the latest move was in the interest of the two countries and based on mutual benefit and respect.  Israel firm among four start-ups to pilot smart solutions at Konza  Speaker Lusaka on removed Senator Mwaura’s BBI vote  Frosty Kenya-Somalia relations leave miraa business in jeopardy   KenyaRe, ScanGroup delay release of results “In the interest of good neighbourliness, Federal Government of Somalia resumes Diplomatic ties with Kenya based on mutual benefit and respect for sovereignty, territorial integrity, non-external interference, peaceful co-existence and equality,” he said.  Hashi said President Farmaajo and his Kenyan counterpart Uhuru Kenyatta were grateful to the Emir of Qatar for his intervention which saw the two agree.    Take a quick survey and help us improve our website!  What Next for learners after KCSE 2020? Analyzing KCSE results 2020 with education experts  Globe marks World Lupus Day as 700,000 Kenyans estimated to be living with Lupus  Motorists concerned as number of road accidents along Nairobi's southern by-pass increase By Winfrey Owino | 1 hour ago By Phares Mutembei | 2 hours ago By Patrick Vidija | 2 hours ago By Patrick Vidija | 6 hours ago